# Vue Components (Tauri/Vue 3 + TypeScript)

## Structure — always in this order
```
<script setup lang="ts">
<template>
<style scoped>
```
No Options API. No class components.

## Script
- `defineProps` with explicit TypeScript types, not runtime validators.
- `defineEmits` typed: `defineEmits<{ update: [value: string] }>()`.
- Composables for logic > 15 lines. Don't inline complex logic in setup.
- `ref` for primitives, `reactive` for objects — don't mix arbitrarily.
- No `any`. Use `unknown` + type guard if type is unclear.

## Template
- One root element or Fragment (`<template>` wrapper), never extra `<div>` wrappers.
- `v-for` always has `:key`. Key must be a stable id, not index.
- No logic in template beyond ternary. Extract to computed if longer.
- Event handlers: `@click="handler"` — no inline lambdas unless one-liner.

## IPC calls from components
- Never call `invoke()` directly inside a component.
- All `invoke()` calls go in composables (`use*.ts`) or a service file.
- Handle loading/error state at the composable level, not in the template.

## Styles
- `scoped` always.
- CSS variables for colors/spacing — no hardcoded hex or px magic numbers.
- No `!important`.
